[30;1m20 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m21 | [0m[35m    A session is a global object that is shared around amongst many clients. It[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35m    therefore contains state that is relevant to everyone. There is a lot of[0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35m    state such as the service type and region_name that are only relevant to a[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m    particular client that is using the session. An adapter provides a wrapper[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35m    of client local data around the global session object.[0m
[30;1m26 | [0m[35m[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1232[0m[34m of [0m[33m2217[0m[31m ]--[0m
